source: ## Read matlab image and plot using Python

from scipy.io import loadmat
%matplotlib inline
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

import mpld3
from mpld3 import plugins
mpld3.enable_notebook()
#matlab header info plus array in dictionary format

# Gray Image
fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,8))
plt.imshow(mat_array, cmap = plt.get_cmap('gray'))
ax.set_title('Tasman Image Grey')
plugins.clear(fig)  # clear all plugins from the figure
plugins.connect(fig, plugins.Reset(), plugins.Zoom(), plugins.MousePosition(fontsize=16, fmt='.4g'))
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Gray Image Crop
fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,10))
plt.imshow(mat_array[500:900,450:700], cmap = plt.get_cmap('gray'))
ax.set_title('Tasman Image Gray')
plt.show()

# Spectral Image Interpolated
fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))
plt.imshow(mat_array, cmap = plt.get_cmap('spectral'), interpolation='bilinear')
ax.set_title('Tasman Image Spectral')
plt.show()
mat_array[1,0:].shape # all the columns in row 2
mat_array[:,1].shape # all the rows in column 2

fig,ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))
plt.imshow(mat_array, cmap = plt.get_cmap('gray'), interpolation='bilinear')
plt.contour(mat_array, [0, 8000], colors = 'red')
plt.show()
